### Component Patterns

#### Functional Components with TypeScript
```typescript
interface ComponentProps {
  title: string
  onAction: (data: any) => void
  children?: React.ReactNode
}

export default function MyComponent({ title, onAction, children }: ComponentProps) {
  const [state, setState] = useState<StateType>(initialState)
  
  return (
    <div className="component-container">
      {/* Component content */}
    </div>
  )
}
```

#### Context Integration
Components use context providers for global state:

```typescript
import { useAssignments } from '@/contexts/AssignmentContext'
import { useQuestionBank } from '@/contexts/QuestionBankContext'

const { assignments, createAssignment } = useAssignments()
const { questions, addQuestion } = useQuestionBank()
```

## UI Component System

### shadcn/ui Foundation
**Base Components**: [src/components/ui/](mdc:src/components/ui/)

Core components include:
- **Button** - Multiple variants (default, destructive, outline, ghost)
- **Card** - Content containers with header/content/footer
